io.odysz.semantic

Class DATranscxt

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.odysz.transact.sql.Transcxt
      • io.odysz.semantic.DATranscxt

  • public class DATranscxt
extends io.odysz.transact.sql.Transcxt
    Statement manager that providing statements with overridden callback methods.

    Those statements are the starting points to build a sql transact for querying, updating, etc.
    For how to use the created statements, see the testing class: DASemantextTest.

    This manager can handling semantics configured in xml. See loadSemantics(String, String).
    Every sql building needing semantics handling must use a context instance created by instancontxt(IUser).
    Author:
    odys-z@github.com

      • DATranscxt

        public DATranscxt(String conn)
           throws SemanticException,
                  SQLException,
                  SAXException,
                  IOException
        Create a transact builder with basic DASemantext instance. It's a null configuration, so semantics can not been resolved, but can be used to do basic sql operation. When creating DATranscxt, db metas can not be null.
        Parameters:
        conn - connection Id
        Throws:
        SemanticException - meta is null
        SQLException
        IOException - load semantics configuration failed
        SAXException - load semantics configuration failed
